30#include <nvif/object.h>
31#include <nvif/client.h>
32#include <nvif/driver.h>
33#include <nvif/ioctl.h>
34
35int
36nvif_object_ioctl(struct nvif_object *object, void *data, u32 size, void **hack)
37{
38 struct nvif_client *client = object->client;
39 union {
40 struct nvif_ioctl_v0 v0;
41 } *args = data;
42
43 if (size >= sizeof(*args) && args->v0.version == 0) {
44 if (object != &client->object)
45 args->v0.object = nvif_handle(object);
46 else
47 args->v0.object = 0;
48 args->v0.owner = NVIF_IOCTL_V0_OWNER_ANY;
49 } else
50 return -ENOSYS;
51
52 return client->driver->ioctl(client->object.priv, client->super,
53 data, size, hack);
54}
55
56void
57nvif_object_sclass_put(struct nvif_sclass **psclass)
58{
59 kfree(*psclass);
60 *psclass = NULL;
61}
62
63int
64nvif_object_sclass_get(struct nvif_object *object, struct nvif_sclass **psclass)
65{
66 struct {
67 struct nvif_ioctl_v0 ioctl;
68 struct nvif_ioctl_sclass_v0 sclass;
69 } *args = NULL;
70 int ret, cnt = 0, i;
71 u32 size;
72
73 while (1) {
74 size = sizeof(*args) + cnt * sizeof(args->sclass.oclass[0]);
75 if (!(args = kmalloc(size, GFP_KERNEL)))
76 return -ENOMEM;
77 args->ioctl.version = 0;
78 args->ioctl.type = NVIF_IOCTL_V0_SCLASS;
79 args->sclass.version = 0;
80 args->sclass.count = cnt;
81
82 ret = nvif_object_ioctl(object, args, size, NULL);
83 if (ret == 0 && args->sclass.count <= cnt)
84 break;
85 cnt = args->sclass.count;
86 kfree(args);
87 if (ret != 0)
88 return ret;
89 }
90
91 *psclass = kzalloc(sizeof(**psclass) * args->sclass.count, GFP_KERNEL);
92 if (*psclass) {
93 for (i = 0; i < args->sclass.count; i++) {
94 (*psclass)[i].oclass = args->sclass.oclass[i].oclass;
95 (*psclass)[i].minver = args->sclass.oclass[i].minver;
96 (*psclass)[i].maxver = args->sclass.oclass[i].maxver;
97 }
98 ret = args->sclass.count;
99 } else {
100 ret = -ENOMEM;
101 }
102
103 kfree(args);
104 return ret;
105}

107u32
108nvif_object_rd(struct nvif_object *object, int size, u64 addr)
109{
110 struct {
111 struct nvif_ioctl_v0 ioctl;
112 struct nvif_ioctl_rd_v0 rd;
113 } args = {
114 .ioctl.type = NVIF_IOCTL_V0_RD,
115 .rd.size = size,
116 .rd.addr = addr,
117 };
118 int ret = nvif_object_ioctl(object, &args, sizeof(args), NULL);
119 if (ret) {
120 /*XXX: warn? */
121 return 0;
122 }
123 return args.rd.data;
124}

126void
127nvif_object_wr(struct nvif_object *object, int size, u64 addr, u32 data)
128{
129 struct {
130 struct nvif_ioctl_v0 ioctl;
131 struct nvif_ioctl_wr_v0 wr;
132 } args = {
133 .ioctl.type = NVIF_IOCTL_V0_WR,
134 .wr.size = size,
135 .wr.addr = addr,
136 .wr.data = data,
137 };
138 int ret = nvif_object_ioctl(object, &args, sizeof(args), NULL);
139 if (ret) {
140 /*XXX: warn? */
141 }
142}

144int
145nvif_object_mthd(struct nvif_object *object, u32 mthd, void *data, u32 size)
146{
147 struct {
148 struct nvif_ioctl_v0 ioctl;
149 struct nvif_ioctl_mthd_v0 mthd;
150 } *args;
151 u8 stack[128];
152 int ret;
153
154 if (sizeof(*args) + size > sizeof(stack)) {
155 if (!(args = kmalloc(sizeof(*args) + size, GFP_KERNEL)))
156 return -ENOMEM;
157 } else {
158 args = (void *)stack;
159 }
160 args->ioctl.version = 0;
161 args->ioctl.type = NVIF_IOCTL_V0_MTHD;
162 args->mthd.version = 0;
163 args->mthd.method = mthd;
164
165 memcpy(args->mthd.data, data, size);
166 ret = nvif_object_ioctl(object, args, sizeof(*args) + size, NULL);
167 memcpy(data, args->mthd.data, size);
168 if (args != (void *)stack)
169 kfree(args);
170 return ret;
171}
172
173void
174nvif_object_unmap(struct nvif_object *object)
175{
176 if (object->map.size) {
177 struct nvif_client *client = object->client;
178 struct {
179 struct nvif_ioctl_v0 ioctl;
180 struct nvif_ioctl_unmap unmap;
181 } args = {
182 .ioctl.type = NVIF_IOCTL_V0_UNMAP,
183 };
184
185 if (object->map.ptr) {
186 client->driver->unmap(client, object->map.tag,
187 object->map.handle,
188 object->map.addr,
189 object->map.ptr,
190 object->map.size);
191 object->map.ptr = NULL;
192 }
193
194 nvif_object_ioctl(object, &args, sizeof(args), NULL);
195 object->map.size = 0;
196 }
197}
198
199int
200nvif_object_map(struct nvif_object *object)
201{
202 struct nvif_client *client = object->client;
203 struct {
204 struct nvif_ioctl_v0 ioctl;
205#ifdef __NetBSD__
206 struct nvif_ioctl_map_netbsd_v0 map;
207#else
208 struct nvif_ioctl_map_v0 map;
209#endif
210 } args = {
211#ifdef __NetBSD__
212 .ioctl.type = NVIF_IOCTL_V0_MAP_NETBSD,
213#else
214 .ioctl.type = NVIF_IOCTL_V0_MAP,
215#endif
216 };
217 int ret = nvif_object_ioctl(object, &args, sizeof(args), NULL);
218 if (ret == 0) {
219 object->map.size = args.map.length;
220#ifdef __NetBSD__
221 object->map.tag = args.map.tag;
222 object->map.addr = args.map.handle;
223 ret = client->driver->map(client, args.map.tag,
224 args.map.handle, object->map.size, &object->map.handle,
225 &object->map.ptr);
226 if (ret) {
227 nvif_object_unmap(object);
228 return -ENOMEM;
229 }
230#else
231 object->map.ptr = client->driver->map(client, args.map.handle,
232 object->map.size);
233 if (ret = -ENOMEM, object->map.ptr)
234 return 0;
235 nvif_object_unmap(object);
236#endif
237 }
238 return ret;
239}
240
241void
242nvif_object_fini(struct nvif_object *object)
243{
244 struct {
245 struct nvif_ioctl_v0 ioctl;
246 struct nvif_ioctl_del del;
247 } args = {
248 .ioctl.type = NVIF_IOCTL_V0_DEL,
249 };
250
251 if (!object->client)
252 return;
253
254 nvif_object_unmap(object);
255 nvif_object_ioctl(object, &args, sizeof(args), NULL);
256 object->client = NULL;
257}
258
259int
260nvif_object_init(struct nvif_object *parent, u32 handle, s32 oclass,
261 void *data, u32 size, struct nvif_object *object)
262{
263 struct {
264 struct nvif_ioctl_v0 ioctl;
265 struct nvif_ioctl_new_v0 new;
266 } *args;
267 int ret = 0;
268
269 object->client = NULL;
270 object->handle = handle;
271 object->oclass = oclass;
272 object->map.ptr = NULL;
273 object->map.size = 0;
274
275 if (parent) {
276 if (!(args = kmalloc(sizeof(*args) + size, GFP_KERNEL))) {
277 nvif_object_fini(object);
278 return -ENOMEM;
279 }
280
281 args->ioctl.version = 0;
282 args->ioctl.type = NVIF_IOCTL_V0_NEW;
283 args->new.version = 0;
284 args->new.route = parent->client->route;
285 args->new.token = nvif_handle(object);
286 args->new.object = nvif_handle(object);
287 args->new.handle = handle;
288 args->new.oclass = oclass;
289
290 memcpy(args->new.data, data, size);
291 ret = nvif_object_ioctl(parent, args, sizeof(*args) + size,
292 &object->priv);
293 memcpy(data, args->new.data, size);
294 kfree(args);
295 if (ret == 0)
296 object->client = parent->client;
297 }
298
299 if (ret)
300 nvif_object_fini(object);
301 return ret;
302}
